## 6. RISKS / EDGE CASES

### Failed Payments
- PaymentIntent created but player closes app before completing: intent expires after 1 hour (Stripe default); booking never inserted; spot not held
- Stripe `.failed` result: show error, do not insert booking, do not decrement credits
- Network loss mid-payment: StripePaymentSheet handles retry internally; only call booking insert on `.completed`

### Partial States
- Booking inserted but credit deduction fails: wrap in a server-side transaction or RPC; rollback booking if credit write fails
- Stripe charge succeeds but booking DB insert fails: idempotency key on PaymentIntent (use `gameID+userID`); retry insert on app relaunch by checking existing payment intents
- Club loses Stripe Connect access mid-game: validate `payouts_enabled` before allowing new paid game creation; existing bookings unaffected

### Credit Misuse
- Race condition on credit application (double-spend): use Postgres `UPDATE player_credits SET amount_cents = amount_cents - $1 WHERE user_id = $2 AND amount_cents >= $1` — returns 0 rows if insufficient; reject atomically
- Admin-adjusted credits: all credit transactions logged with `reason`; audit trail available
- Credit balance going negative: enforced by the atomic update guard above

### Subscription Limits
- Club exceeds game/member limit after downgrade: existing data preserved; block new creation with clear upgrade prompt
- Subscription payment fails (Stripe dunning): webhook sets tier to `free` after grace period; notify club owner via push + email
- Club owner deletes account while subscribed: cancel Stripe subscription in `delete-club` flow; pro-rate refund policy TBD

